"{\"uid\": \"si.com-tennis-tennis-mailbag-rafael-nadal-carlos-alcaraz-capture-2024-olympics-buzz\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Hey everyone \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 I hope you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re enjoying the Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 55, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2 Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the latest episode ofServed with Andy Roddick.\", \"from\": 57, \"to\": 116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 103, \"end\": 115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Roddick\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andy Roddick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Roddick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Roddick\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because it is 2024, and dignity can be a sparse commodity, I am obliged to tell you to smash the like button and subscribe, rate and review.\", \"from\": 117, \"to\": 257, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am also duty-bound to invite you to our live show in Cincinnati on Aug. 8, the Friday before the tournament.\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cincinnati_Masters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.979275658142029e-27, \"text\": \"Cincinnati\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cincinnati_Masters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cincinnati_Masters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2 A few of you asked about the Cape Town College of Magic piece that aired on60 Minutesthe other night.\", \"from\": 370, \"to\": 475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099sa clip.\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 491, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2 A reminder that Jay Caspian Kang\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s30 for 30documentary on Michael Chang,American Son, premieres this week on ESPN.Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099sthe trailer.\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 517, \"end\": 524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caspian_Sea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.219152443554983e-17, \"text\": \"Caspian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caspian_Sea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caspian_Sea\"}, {\"begin\": 557, \"end\": 570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Chang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Chang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Chang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Chang\"}, {\"begin\": 571, \"end\": 583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iron_Patriot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1134450745568818e-17, \"text\": \"American Son\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iron_Patriot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iron_Patriot\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Onward \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6  Jon,\\u00c2  As a longtime Rafael Nadal fan, all I can say at this point is this is painful.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 668, \"end\": 680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafael Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please make it stop.\\u00c2  Respectfully,\\u00c2  Dominic Ciafardini, Westchester, NY  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2Yeah \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 about that.\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 806, \"end\": 808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.824443074698828e-40, \"text\": \"NY\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is like a hooking (lefty) passing shot.\", \"from\": 834, \"to\": 878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a needle to thread here.\\u00c2  It is a Hague-violating international crime to tell athletes it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s time to quit.\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 996, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Years are added to your sentence for adding the phrase \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009ctarnishing your legacy.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d This isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t presidential politics where age impacts performance, that affects millions.\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In an individual sport in particular, if Venus Williams or Tiger Woods or Nadal or Stan Wawrinka or whoever wants to play and find fulfillment until they are AARP-eligible, so be it.\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1212, \"end\": 1226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venus_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Venus Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venus_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venus_Williams\"}, {\"begin\": 1230, \"end\": 1241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiger_Woods\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.950701593210525e-70, \"text\": \"Tiger Woods\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiger_Woods\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiger_Woods\"}, {\"begin\": 1245, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.766024237297745e-26, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 1254, \"end\": 1267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stan_Wawrinka\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stan Wawrinka\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stan_Wawrinka\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stan_Wawrinka\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Live your best life; live your longest career.\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t mean it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not jarring to watch the decline, nor that we should ignore what we are seeing.\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In his prime, Nadal was\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094I credit Bob Bryan for first using this descriptive\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009ca beast.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d There was, at once, this ferocity and nobility to his tennis.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1523, \"end\": 1528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.766024237297745e-26, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 1544, \"end\": 1547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6256698440814444e-22, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\"}, {\"begin\": 1548, \"end\": 1553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Bryan\", \"score\": 0.9847825926497025, \"rank\": 0.015452555177084574, \"text\": \"Bryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Bryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Bryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His record spoke/screamed volumes.\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Especially at Roland Garros.\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, watching him return to that venue and struggle to win points on serve at times was \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 unnerving.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In May, hewasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t quite there against Alexander Zverev.\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1872, \"end\": 1888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_Zverev\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.606284524420203e-69, \"text\": \"Alexander Zverev\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_Zverev\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_Zverev\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he was playing his first match in months.\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1935, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was nearly 38.\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 1953, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was playing a top-flight opponent a decade his junior.\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 2011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Monday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s outingagainst Novak Djokovicwas difficult to watch.\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Fortunately for him, at least in the U.S., it was, literally, difficult to watch.)\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His shots didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t penetrate.\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His serve was a nonfactor.\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His movement was compromised.\", \"from\": 2217, \"to\": 2246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Though he and Djokovic are not even a year apart in age, they looked like they were from different generations.\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2261, \"end\": 2269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3799627102582158e-27, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(At times, it looked like they were playing a different version of the same sport.)\", \"from\": 2359, \"to\": 2442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nadal is a legend.\", \"from\": 2444, \"to\": 2462, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Literally.\", \"from\": 2463, \"to\": 2473, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As in: He has inspired a body of historic stories.\", \"from\": 2474, \"to\": 2524, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He leaves the stage when he wants to.\", \"from\": 2525, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He calls the shots.\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t preclude us from acknowledging, regrettably, how far the present looks from the past.\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2683, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If someone hasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t already brought this up, should [Carlos] Alcaraz win gold, we should call it the Channel Triple Crown.\\u00c2  In order to differentiate Olympic tennis, perhaps there could be a team format.\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Figure skating has both a team and individual events and it works well.\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2961, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Borrow from World Team Tennis if needed; shorten the sets, and make national representation truly mean something.\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 3075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2974, \"end\": 2991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_TeamTennis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Team Tennis\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_TeamTennis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_TeamTennis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps it would encourage the top names to play mixed as well!\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jay O.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2 Well played.\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Channel Triple Crown, it is.\", \"from\": 3166, \"to\": 3194, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What if Alcaraz wins the U.S. Open?\", \"from\": 3195, \"to\": 3230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3203, \"end\": 3210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5405688396700228e-28, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Summer Triple Crown?\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3255, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He will have three on the trot, on three surfaces.\", \"from\": 3256, \"to\": 3306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Neither Roger Federer nor Djokovic achieved this feat.\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3315, \"end\": 3328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roger Federer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\"}, {\"begin\": 3333, \"end\": 3341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3799627102582158e-27, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nadal did it in 2010.\", \"from\": 3362, \"to\": 3383, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I sense Olympic tennis is getting beaten up a bit this week.\", \"from\": 3385, \"to\": 3445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t quite get it.\", \"from\": 3446, \"to\": 3469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sure, it would be preferable if doubles players were thrown in as singles replacements.\", \"from\": 3470, \"to\": 3557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(I have a lot of respect for my old Amsterdam neighbor, Robin Haase; but I did a double-take seeing him, ranked 1199, in the singles draw!)\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3594, \"end\": 3603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.862403588941505e-19, \"text\": \"Amsterdam\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\"}, {\"begin\": 3614, \"end\": 3625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robin_Haase\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Robin Haase\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robin_Haase\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robin_Haase\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But what choice is there?\", \"from\": 3698, \"to\": 3723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have lucky losers at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3724, \"to\": 3770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And sure, some top players took passes.\", \"from\": 3772, \"to\": 3811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But notthatmany.\", \"from\": 3812, \"to\": 3828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(And I suspect there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s some FOMO from those who were eligible and passed.)\", \"from\": 3829, \"to\": 3905, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More on this below.\", \"from\": 3906, \"to\": 3925, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And an overall team event doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t really work for, say, Iga Swiatek or Djokovic.\", \"from\": 3927, \"to\": 4009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3985, \"end\": 3988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2193321927587014e-23, \"text\": \"Iga\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 4000, \"end\": 4008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3799627102582158e-27, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Should they be denied when there are no Polish men and Serbian women, respectively, in the field?\", \"from\": 4010, \"to\": 4107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4050, \"end\": 4056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_language\", \"score\": 0.9627246164498824, \"rank\": 0.03863817743002702, \"text\": \"Polish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4065, \"end\": 4072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.8995641827219448, \"rank\": 0.1007371387449049, \"text\": \"Serbian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like many of you, I wish it were prioritized by broadcast decision-makers.\", \"from\": 4109, \"to\": 4183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m all-in on Olympic tennis.\", \"from\": 4184, \"to\": 4219, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And suspect most fans are as well.\", \"from\": 4220, \"to\": 4254, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If [Djokovic] had beaten Nadal 6\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00931 6\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00930 he would have been roundly criticized as an ass.\", \"from\": 4256, \"to\": 4347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"J.B, Portland  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2 Yes, probably from the social media mafia.\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I think most true/sane/sentient fans understand that A) few losing opponentswantcharity or mercy and B) especially with dangerous opponents\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and 22-time major winners at their venue of choice certainly meet this description\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094you cannot start handing out games.\", \"from\": 4411, \"to\": 4677, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To be clear: Nadal won those additional games.\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 4725, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4692, \"end\": 4697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.766024237297745e-26, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Djokovic gave no charity.\", \"from\": 4726, \"to\": 4751, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But if he had closed it out 6\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00931, 6\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00930, he would simply have been doing his job.\", \"from\": 4752, \"to\": 4834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And doing it well.\\u00c2  Hey Jon!\", \"from\": 4835, \"to\": 4864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two, tangentially related questions for you.\", \"from\": 4866, \"to\": 4910, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"1) Do you think (or have you heard murmurings) that Swiatek\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s dominance on clay is one of the reasons for so many high-profile DNPs at the Olympics?\", \"from\": 4911, \"to\": 5061, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a subtle difference to me between Ben Shelton preparing for hardcourt, rightly feeling that clay doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t suit him best, and someone like [Aryna] Sabalenka\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094one of the best players in the world, who maybe feels like she should get ready for the Open instead of a playing a tournament where could AT BEST get the silver medal.\\u00c2  2) Speaking of medals, at what point do you think most players would value an Olympic victory over a slam?\", \"from\": 5062, \"to\": 5508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5106, \"end\": 5117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Shelton\", \"score\": 0.9999837952540147, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ben Shelton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Shelton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Shelton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I assume the vast majority of players would much rather bag a major than get gold at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 5509, \"to\": 5607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel that MOST players would rather sayI made the finals of a majorthan get silver.\", \"from\": 5608, \"to\": 5693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But how might they compare making a slam semifinal to winning the bronze?\", \"from\": 5694, \"to\": 5767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"-n from California  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2 I think the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympic field is quite strong and quite logical\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094as an athlete from Belarus, Sabalenka\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s appearance was always going to be problematic.\", \"from\": 5769, \"to\": 5953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5777, \"end\": 5787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999756560808283, \"rank\": 2.2743151831891012e-05, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}, {\"begin\": 5884, \"end\": 5891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"score\": 0.9999999946921889, \"rank\": 5.307981329440592e-09, \"text\": \"Belarus\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is informed speculation but as an athlete who not only struggles with her health, but was born in Moscow\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and whose Wimbledon title in 2022 was curdled a bit by questions of her nationality\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Elena Rybakina\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s late withdrawal was not a surprise.\", \"from\": 5954, \"to\": 6206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"C) Even if Swiatek were going in as the overwhelming favorite, you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d think the Olympics are singularly well-suited for additional entries.\", \"from\": 6207, \"to\": 6347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike regular events, you can leave with a silver or bronze medal!\", \"from\": 6348, \"to\": 6415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Talking to players about this, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s clear that the overwhelming majority would value a singles major above\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094if slightly\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094an Olympic gold.\", \"from\": 6417, \"to\": 6558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I would submit that a doubles gold in the Games would mean more to most players than a major title.\", \"from\": 6559, \"to\": 6662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2 Speaking of doubles, here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s an omnibus \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 There was a bit of chatter last month about doubles, its future and what many thought was dismissive treatment on aServedpodcast episode.\", \"from\": 6664, \"to\": 6850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m not sure I want to enter the fray.\", \"from\": 6852, \"to\": 6892, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, I know I don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t.\", \"from\": 6893, \"to\": 6919, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the deal: Tennis should be able to accommodate doubles.\", \"from\": 6920, \"to\": 6988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Matches are entertaining.\", \"from\": 6989, \"to\": 7014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They feature so many virtues\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094net play, angles, scrambling, teamwork\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094that fans love and, purportedly, miss from so many singles matches.\", \"from\": 7015, \"to\": 7154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More crassly: Tennis\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094like any healthy industry\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094should be adding, not shedding jobs.\", \"from\": 7155, \"to\": 7242, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And, at a minimum, doubles matches are necessary to fill sessions.\", \"from\": 7243, \"to\": 7309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We have these prolonged ATP Masters series events which span nearly two weeks.\", \"from\": 7310, \"to\": 7388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Especially on those slow second-week days, you need acts on stage.\", \"from\": 7389, \"to\": 7455, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the same time, there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s this reality: Doubles isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t punching through.\", \"from\": 7457, \"to\": 7532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Matches don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t rate or draw fans.\", \"from\": 7533, \"to\": 7567, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Singles stars seldom play, despite various inducements.\", \"from\": 7568, \"to\": 7623, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Someone made the point that at Wimbledon, the No.1 doubles player at the time\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009444-year-old Rohan Bopanna\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094lost early.\", \"from\": 7624, \"to\": 7743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7716, \"end\": 7721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Dragon_Prince\", \"score\": 0.995033416151711, \"rank\": 0.004350255760127741, \"text\": \"Rohan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Dragon_Prince\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Dragon_Prince\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And this upset went wholly unacknowledged.\", \"from\": 7744, \"to\": 7786, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a chicken-and-egg problem.\", \"from\": 7788, \"to\": 7824, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The doubles players complain that the ATP has not properly invested in marketing the product.\", \"from\": 7825, \"to\": 7918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7863, \"end\": 7866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Association_of_Tennis_Professionals\", \"score\": 0.9999643553233045, \"rank\": 3.559033566206984e-05, \"text\": \"ATP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Association_of_Tennis_Professionals\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Association_of_Tennis_Professionals\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ATP\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094factions of it, anyway\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094respond that the market has spoken and there is no sense investing in the product.\", \"from\": 7919, \"to\": 8036, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, we get \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cinnovations\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d likemic-ing up players.\", \"from\": 8037, \"to\": 8094, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Usually, we saysomething\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gotta give.\", \"from\": 8096, \"to\": 8136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But this has been the liminal state of doubles for decades.\", \"from\": 8137, \"to\": 8196, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I suspect this will continue.\", \"from\": 8197, \"to\": 8230, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ATP won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t euthanize doubles.\", \"from\": 8231, \"to\": 8265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8235, \"end\": 8238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Association_of_Tennis_Professionals\", \"score\": 0.9999643553233045, \"rank\": 3.559033566206984e-05, \"text\": \"ATP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Association_of_Tennis_Professionals\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Association_of_Tennis_Professionals\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t make an additional investment.\", \"from\": 8266, \"to\": 8311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It will not alter the scheduling and scoring to encourage more singles to enter.\", \"from\": 8312, \"to\": 8392, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And so it goes \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6  Hi Jon,  I watched your interview with Elena Rybakina before her Wimbledon semifinal match.\", \"from\": 8393, \"to\": 8504, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8452, \"end\": 8466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elena_Rybakina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elena Rybakina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elena_Rybakina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elena_Rybakina\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I thought yourRed Bull questionwas a good one.\", \"from\": 8505, \"to\": 8551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She (and all tennis players) get asked the same questions at every turn.\", \"from\": 8552, \"to\": 8624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It must be nice to get an unusual question now and then.\", \"from\": 8625, \"to\": 8681, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If I were her, at some point in the conversation, I would have said:  I have a question for you.\", \"from\": 8682, \"to\": 8778, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I read a tennis columnist's predictions before the tournament started.\", \"from\": 8779, \"to\": 8849, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He predicted that the final four would be [Swiatek], Coco [Gauff], Sabalenka and [Lucia] Bronzetti.\", \"from\": 8850, \"to\": 8949, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It turns out that he got all four wrong.\\u00c2\\u00a0 Any comment?\", \"from\": 8950, \"to\": 9005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If she had asked you (and I am sure she's far too nice to do that), what would you have said?\", \"from\": 9007, \"to\": 9100, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's [another] question for your mailbag:  The pros talk about playing practice sets with each other.\", \"from\": 9102, \"to\": 9205, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In real sets, they never speak before or during the match and rarely acknowledge each other unless the other player hits a tremendous shot.\", \"from\": 9206, \"to\": 9345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What are practice sets like?\", \"from\": 9346, \"to\": 9374, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Salvage63  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2 A) \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cElena, I am leaden with shame.\", \"from\": 9376, \"to\": 9427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I picked three top-four players and the one I neglected\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094you!\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094went furthest.\", \"from\": 9428, \"to\": 9507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And Bronzetti was silly.\", \"from\": 9508, \"to\": 9532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Next time I will swig a Red Bull before projecting.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  B) It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s funny, I always thought of practice sets as fairly pro forma.\", \"from\": 9533, \"to\": 9660, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t much predictive value.\", \"from\": 9661, \"to\": 9698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And, if anything, they often throw off the scent.Daniil Medvedev smoked Djokovic in a practice set!Then, when they play for real, the outcome is the precise opposite.\", \"from\": 9699, \"to\": 9865, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9794, \"end\": 9798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scheme_(programming_language)\", \"score\": 0.9999992330425115, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"set!\", \"types\": [\"Q9143\", \"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scheme_(programming_language)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scheme_(programming_language)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But then I heard Gauff at Wimbledon talking about players taking practice seriously, to the extent that some players (not Jelena Ostapenko, she volunteered!)\", \"from\": 9867, \"to\": 10024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9989, \"end\": 10005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Je\\u013cena_Ostapenko\", \"score\": 0.9999999957772161, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jelena Ostapenko\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Je\\u013cena_Ostapenko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Je\\u013cena_Ostapenko\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"even call a tight line.\", \"from\": 10025, \"to\": 10048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So now, I will reconsider practice sets and watch them more closely.\", \"from\": 10049, \"to\": 10117, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If Vijay [Amritraj] can get into the Hall of Fame, then Vitas [Gerulaitis] should be in no questions asked.\", \"from\": 10119, \"to\": 10226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10175, \"end\": 10180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vitas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vitas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vitas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vitas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"@jt_spurs  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a2 Sure.\", \"from\": 10228, \"to\": 10248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A few of you asked how Amritraj made the Hall of Fame when he never advanced beyond the quarters of a major and his highest ranking was 18.\", \"from\": 10249, \"to\": 10388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The short answer: this was more about his contributions to the sport, opening the portals to India (population: 1.4 billion) than his record.\", \"from\": 10389, \"to\": 10530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10482, \"end\": 10487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.6325393452135444, \"rank\": 0.5809292546016909, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Note hiseloquent induction speechhere.\", \"from\": 10531, \"to\": 10569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If Gerulaitis were a ballot under similar circumstances\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094his overall contributions deserve this measure of recognition\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094I suspect it would be received enthusiastically.\", \"from\": 10570, \"to\": 10740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ENJOY THE FINAL ROUNDS FROM PARIS, EVERYONE!\", \"from\": 10742, \"to\": 10786, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 10788, \"to\": 10814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Jon Wertheim is a senior writer for Sports Illustrated and has been part of the full-time SI writing staff since 1997, largely focusing on the tennis beat, sports business and social issues, and enterprise journalism.\", \"from\": 10815, \"to\": 11096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10879, \"end\": 10891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Wertheim\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jon Wertheim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Wertheim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Wertheim\"}, {\"begin\": 10915, \"end\": 10933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.287279521330584e-41, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to his work at SI, he is a correspondent for \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009c60 Minutes\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and a commentator for The Tennis Channel.\", \"from\": 11097, \"to\": 11212, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has authored 11 books and has been honored with two Emmys, numerous writing and investigative journalism awards, and the Eugene Scott Award from the International Tennis Hall of Fame.\", \"from\": 11213, \"to\": 11399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11268, \"end\": 11273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmy_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999999999763531, \"rank\": 2.3722090739782736e-11, \"text\": \"Emmys\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmy_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmy_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 11337, \"end\": 11349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gene_Scott\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2407402862372619e-36, \"text\": \"Eugene Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gene_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gene_Scott\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wertheim is a longtime member of the New York Bar Association (retired), the International Tennis Writers Association and the Writers Guild of America.\", \"from\": 11400, \"to\": 11551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11437, \"end\": 11445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999999836291, \"rank\": 1.6525179495248348e-11, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 11437, \"end\": 11461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_State_Bar_Association\", \"score\": 0.9795546287903171, \"rank\": 0.020872109230535157, \"text\": \"New York Bar Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_State_Bar_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_State_Bar_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 11491, \"end\": 11497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9646743831712097e-24, \"text\": \"Tennis\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has a bachelor\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in history from Yale University and received a law degree from the University of Pennsylvania.\", \"from\": 11552, \"to\": 11668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11590, \"end\": 11605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yale_University\", \"score\": 0.9999999888959793, \"rank\": 1.1027647470573106e-08, \"text\": \"Yale University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yale_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yale_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He resides in New York City and Paris with his wife, who is a divorce mediator and adjunct law professor.\", \"from\": 11669, \"to\": 11774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11683, \"end\": 11696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.899169474814285e-18, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 11701, \"end\": 11706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.149592814615449e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have two children.\", \"from\": 11775, \"to\": 11798, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC.\", \"from\": 11800, \"to\": 11877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 11878, \"to\": 11900, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only.\", \"from\": 11901, \"to\": 11977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands.\", \"from\": 11978, \"to\": 12172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12105, \"end\": 12123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.287279521330584e-41, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit.\", \"from\": 12173, \"to\": 12261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\", \"from\": 12262, \"to\": 12394, \"entities\": []}]}"